<html><head><title>AsteroidMeta: A scholium-based document model</title><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="wiki.css" /><meta name="robots" content="INDEX,NOFOLLOW" /><link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="AsteroidMeta" href="index.html@action=rss" /><link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="AsteroidMeta: A_scholium-based_document_model" href="?action=rss;rcidonly=A_scholium-based_document_model" /></head><body class=""><div class="header"><span class="gotobar bar"><a class="local" href="HomePage">HomePage</a> <a class="local" href="RecentChanges">RecentChanges</a> </span><div class="message"><p>(redirected from <a class="edit" title="Click to edit this page" href="?action=edit;id=scholium_system">scholium system</a>)</p></div><h1><a title="Click to search for references to this page" href="?search=A+scholium-based+document+model">A scholium-based document model</a></h1></div><div class="content browse"><dl class="quote"><dt /><dd>"Love me or hate me, it's still an obsession" &#x2013; Lady Sovereign, 2006</dd></dl><h1>Arxana</h1><p>Arxana is a content management and hypertext editing platform, based on the idea of robust and universal annotation.</p><p>Arxana can do a number of useful things the current <a class="local" href="/No%c3%b6sphere">No√∂sphere</a> can't do. However, the reverse is also true (for now). Our current development objective is to bridge the gaps between these two systems, and in so doing, prepare Arxana for full-scale deployment.</p><p>The current development version of the system is available for preliminary testing, experimentation, and constructive criticism.</p><p>For a quick "tech notes"-style summary of where this project is at right now (as of Dec 18, 2006), see <a class="local" href="/Arxana_overview">Arxana overview</a>!</p><hr /><p><a class="local" href="/HDM_CVS">How to get the latest version</a> | <a class="local" href="/first_introduction_to_scholium_systems">first introduction to scholium systems</a> | <a class="url outside" href="http://br.endernet.org/~akrowne/planetmath/papers/corneli_fcdl/">an introductory conference paper</a> | <a class="local" href="/Arxana_News">Arxana News</a> | <a class="local" href="/old_draft_of_scholium_system">preliminary writeup</a> | <a class="local" href="/discussion_of_old_draft_of_scholium_system">comments on preliminary writeup</a></p><hr /><h1>Related discussions</h1><ul><li><a class="local" href="/the_spirit_of_the_scholium_system">the spirit of the scholium system</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/using_the_scholium_system">using the scholium system</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/type_creation_and_the_scholium_system">type creation and the scholium system</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/discussion_of_the_submitted_scholium_system_abstract">discussion of the submitted scholium system abstract</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/scholia_and_knowledge_communities">scholia and knowledge communities</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/the_scholium_system_and_AI">the scholium system and AI</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/social%2c_political%2c_and_economic_scholium_systems">social, political, and economic scholium systems</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/inspirations_for_the_scholium_system">inspirations for the scholium system</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/scholia_and_literary_machines">scholia and literary machines</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/historical_scholia_systems">historical scholia systems</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/submitted_version_of_scholium_paper">submitted version of scholium paper</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/software_patents_and_the_scholium_system">software patents and the scholium system</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/text_property_problems">text property problems</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/scholium_system_and_free_software">scholium system and free software</a></li><li><a class="local" href="/arxana%2c_the_scholium_system">arxana, the schol